verses.text_plain: Then Job answered and said,
verses.verse_html: 1Then Job answered and said,

verses.text_plain: I know it is so of a truth: but how should man be just with God?
verses.verse_html:
2I know it is so of a truth: but how should man be just with God? ▼
▼ with God: or, before God?

footnotes.body_html: ▼ with God: or, before God?

verses.text_plain: If he will contend with him, he cannot answer him one of a thousand.
verses.verse_html: 3If he will contend with him, he cannot answer him one of a thousand.

verses.text_plain: He is wise in heart, and mighty in strength: who hath hardened himself against him, and hath prospered?
verses.verse_html: 4He is wise in heart, and mighty in strength: who hath hardened himself against him, and hath prospered?

verses.text_plain: Which removeth the mountains, and they know not: which overturneth them in his anger.
verses.verse_html: 5Which removeth the mountains, and they know not: which overturneth them in his anger.

verses.text_plain: Which shaketh the earth out of her place, and the pillars thereof tremble.
verses.verse_html: 6Which shaketh the earth out of her place, and the pillars thereof tremble.

verses.text_plain: Which commandeth the sun, and it riseth not; and sealeth up the stars.
verses.verse_html: 7Which commandeth the sun, and it riseth not; and sealeth up the stars.

verses.text_plain: Which alone spreadeth out the heavens, and treadeth upon the waves of the sea.
verses.verse_html:
8Which alone spreadeth out the heavens, and treadeth upon the waves of the sea. ▼
▼ waves: Heb. heights

verses.text_plain: Which maketh Arcturus, Orion, and Pleiades, and the chambers of the south.
verses.verse_html:
9Which maketh Arcturus, Orion, and Pleiades, and the chambers of the south. ▼
▼ Arcturus…: Heb. Ash, Cesil, and Cimah

footnotes.body_text: ▼ Arcturus…: Heb. Ash, Cesil, and Cimah
footnotes.body_html: ▼ Arcturus…: Heb. Ash, Cesil, and Cimah

verses.text_plain: Which doeth great things past finding out; yea, and wonders without number.
verses.verse_html: 10Which doeth great things past finding out; yea, and wonders without number.

verses.text_plain: Lo, he goeth by me, and I see him not: he passeth on also, but I perceive him not.
verses.verse_html: 11Lo, he goeth by me, and I see him not: he passeth on also, but I perceive him not.

verses.text_plain: Behold, he taketh away, who can hinder him? who will say unto him, What doest thou?
verses.verse_html:
12Behold, he taketh away, who can hinder him? who will say unto him, What doest thou? ▼
▼ hinder…: Heb. turn him away?

footnotes.body_html: ▼ hinder…: Heb. turn him away?

verses.text_plain: If God will not withdraw his anger, the proud helpers do stoop under him.
verses.verse_html:
13If God will not withdraw his anger, the proud helpers do stoop under him. ▼
▼ proud…: Heb. helpers of pride, or, strength

footnotes.body_text: ▼ proud…: Heb. helpers of pride, or, strength
footnotes.body_html: ▼ proud…: Heb. helpers of pride, or, strength

verses.text_plain: How much less shall I answer him, and choose out my words to reason with him?
verses.verse_html: 14How much less shall I answer him, and choose out my words to reason with him?

tokens.text: How much less shall I answer

verses.text_plain: Whom, though I were righteous, yet would I not answer, but I would make supplication to my judge.
verses.verse_html: 15Whom, though I were righteous, yet would I not answer, but I would make supplication to my judge.

verses.text_plain: If I had called, and he had answered me; yet would I not believe that he had hearkened unto my voice.
verses.verse_html: 16If I had called, and he had answered me; yet would I not believe that he had hearkened unto my voice.

verses.text_plain: For he breaketh me with a tempest, and multiplieth my wounds without cause.
verses.verse_html: 17For he breaketh me with a tempest, and multiplieth my wounds without cause.

verses.text_plain: He will not suffer me to take my breath, but filleth me with bitterness.
verses.verse_html: 18He will not suffer me to take my breath, but filleth me with bitterness.

verses.text_plain: If I speak of strength, lo, he is strong: and if of judgment, who shall set me a time to plead?
verses.verse_html: 19If I speak of strength, lo, he is strong: and if of judgment, who shall set me a time to plead?

verses.text_plain: If I justify myself, mine own mouth shall condemn me: if I say, I am perfect, it shall also prove me perverse.
verses.verse_html: 20If I justify myself, mine own mouth shall condemn me: if I say, I am perfect, it shall also prove me perverse.

tokens.text: it shall also prove me perverse

verses.text_plain: Though I were perfect, yet would I not know my soul: I would despise my life.
verses.verse_html: 21Though I were perfect, yet would I not know my soul: I would despise my life.

verses.text_plain: This is one thing, therefore I said it, He destroyeth the perfect and the wicked.
verses.verse_html: 22This is one thing, therefore I said it, He destroyeth the perfect and the wicked.

verses.text_plain: If the scourge slay suddenly, he will laugh at the trial of the innocent.
verses.verse_html: 23If the scourge slay suddenly, he will laugh at the trial of the innocent.

verses.text_plain: The earth is given into the hand of the wicked: he covereth the faces of the judges thereof; if not, where, and who is he?
verses.verse_html: 24The earth is given into the hand of the wicked: he covereth the faces of the judges thereof; if not, where, and who is he?

verses.text_plain: Now my days are swifter than a post: they flee away, they see no good.
verses.verse_html: 25Now my days are swifter than a post: they flee away, they see no good.

verses.text_plain: They are passed away as the swift ships: as the eagle that hasteth to the prey.
verses.verse_html:
26They are passed away as the swift ships: as the eagle that hasteth to the prey. ▼
▼ swift…: or, ships of Ebeh: Heb. ships of desire

footnotes.body_text: ▼ swift…: or, ships of Ebeh: Heb. ships of desire
footnotes.body_html: ▼ swift…: or, ships of Ebeh: Heb. ships of desire

verses.text_plain: If I say, I will forget my complaint, I will leave off my heaviness, and comfort myself:
verses.verse_html: 27If I say, I will forget my complaint, I will leave off my heaviness, and comfort myself:

verses.text_plain: I am afraid of all my sorrows, I know that thou wilt not hold me innocent.
verses.verse_html: 28I am afraid of all my sorrows, I know that thou wilt not hold me innocent.

tokens.text: that thou wilt not hold me innocent

verses.text_plain: If I be wicked, why then labour I in vain?
verses.verse_html: 29If I be wicked, why then labour I in vain?

verses.text_plain: If I wash myself with snow water, and make my hands never so clean;
verses.verse_html: 30If I wash myself with snow water, and make my hands never so clean;

verses.text_plain: Yet shalt thou plunge me in the ditch, and mine own clothes shall abhor me.
verses.verse_html:
31Yet shalt thou plunge me in the ditch, and mine own clothes shall abhor me. ▼
▼ abhor…: or, make me to be abhorred

footnotes.body_text: ▼ abhor…: or, make me to be abhorred
footnotes.body_html: ▼ abhor…: or, make me to be abhorred

verses.text_plain: For he is not a man, as I am, that I should answer him, and we should come together in judgment.
verses.verse_html: 32For he is not a man, as I am, that I should answer him, and we should come together in judgment.

verses.text_plain: Neither is there any daysman betwixt us, that might lay his hand upon us both.
verses.verse_html:
33Neither is there any daysman betwixt us, that might lay his hand upon us both. ▼
▼ any…: Heb. one that should argue
 , ▼
▼ daysman: or, umpire

footnotes.body_text: ▼ any…: Heb. one that should argue
footnotes.body_html: ▼ any…: Heb. one that should argue

verses.text_plain: Let him take his rod away from me, and let not his fear terrify me:
verses.verse_html: 34Let him take his rod away from me, and let not his fear terrify me:

tokens.text: from me, and let not his fear

verses.text_plain: Then would I speak, and not fear him; but it is not so with me.
verses.verse_html:
35Then would I speak, and not fear him; but it is not so with me. ▼
▼ it is…: Heb. I am not so with myself

footnotes.body_text: ▼ it is…: Heb. I am not so with myself
footnotes.body_html: ▼ it is…: Heb. I am not so with myself
